    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification provides sufficient confidence in hemolysis predictions. Identified factor gaps are considered acceptable given the conservative safety margins applied in the hemolysis threshold comparison. Assurance level Medium reflects the team's judgment that the overall evidence package, while incomplete in several factors, is adequate for regulatory submission purposes.",
